line_1: And on himself his pensive Fury wroke,
And on himself his pensive Fury wroke,
line_2: Oft, stung by Spleen, at once away he broke,

line_1: And on himself his pensive Fury wroke,
line_2: To Groves of Pine, and broad o'ershadowing Oak;

line_1: "'Tis plain that Anteros his spight has wroke;
"'Tis plain that Anteros his spight has wroke;
line_2: Beg'd her to doff the keenness of her look,

line_1: "'Tis plain that Anteros his spight has wroke;
line_2: Which nature feeling to her center shook.
